editorialSummary.text: Warmly furnished rooms in an informal hotel offering breakfast & a laid-back restaurant.

text.text:
I recently stayed at Hotel Ranbirs in Alambagh and opted for their Twin Bed Room. The location of the hotel is definitely one of its strongest points—especially convenient for air travelers. The Lucknow airport is just a 10–15-minute drive away, making it a great choice for short stopovers or early morning flights. Additionally, there are a number of restaurants in the nearby area, which adds to the convenience. The hotel also has its own in-house restaurant, though I didn't get the chance to try it.

The Twin Bed Room I stayed in was very clean, which is always a plus. However, the room size was extremely compact—I'd estimate it to be under 100 sq. ft. It felt quite cramped, especially for two people. So if you're planning to stay in a twin bed room, I'd suggest thinking it through, particularly if you need a bit more space to feel comfortable.

One major downside was the air conditioning. Despite setting it to 16 degrees Celsius, the room took over an hour to cool down, which was disappointing given the small size of the room. This could be a concern during the hotter months.

On the brighter side, the hotel overall seems well-maintained and offers a good standard of cleanliness. For solo travelers or short stays, especially for those catching flights, it can be a practical and budget-friendly choice. Just be mindful of the room size if you're booking a twin bed room.

In summary, Hotel Ranbirs offers a good location and cleanliness, but room size and AC performance in the twin bed category may leave you wanting more. It’s a decent place for a short stay, but consider your space needs before booking.

I recently stayed at this hotel and was thoroughly impressed! It’s an excellent choice for business travelers and airport commuters, offering compact yet thoughtfully designed rooms with all the essential amenities, making it perfect for overnight or short stays. The affordability truly stood out. You get incredible value for the comfort and convenience provided. The in-house restaurant serves delicious food, and the best part? The prices are the same whether you dine in or opt for room service, which is a rare and welcome perk. The staff was exceptionally cooperative, humble, and went above and beyond to ensure a pleasant experience.
Located near Shringarnagar Metro Station, the hotel is just 15 Minute ride from the airport, adding to its convenience. If you’re looking for a no-fuss, budget-friendly stay with great service, this is the place to be. Highly recommend!
